This paper is about event detection using deep learning methods, which is a common topic in natural language processing (NLP) research. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CL (Computation and Language). The paper also uses recurrent neural networks (RNNs), which are a type of deep learning model, so cs.LG (Machine Learning) is also a likely category. Additionally, the paper involves automatic feature engineering, which is a common topic in artificial intelligence (cs.AI) research. The use of RNNs also suggests that the paper may be relevant to the neural networks (cs.NE) category. Finally, the paper involves information retrieval (IR) tasks, such as identifying relevant events in text, so cs.IR is a possible category as well.
